\title{Implementing Identity Verification For Zero Trust}

\taxon{skill}

\tag{zero-trust}

\tag{identity}

\tag{authentication}

\tag{mfa}

\tag{identity-verification}

\meta{version}{"1.0"}

\meta{description}{Implement continuous identity verification for zero trust using phishing-resistant MFA (FIDO2/WebAuthn), risk-based conditional access, and identity governance aligned with the CISA Zero Trust Maturity Model.}

\subtree{
\title{Implementing Identity Verification for Zero Trust}
\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Understanding of zero trust principles (NIST SP 800-207)}
\li{Familiarity with identity providers (Azure AD, Okta, Ping Identity)}
\li{Knowledge of authentication protocols (SAML 2.0, OIDC, FIDO2)}
\li{Understanding of MFA and passwordless authentication}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Identity is the foundational pillar of zero trust architecture. NIST SP 800-207 mandates that all resource authentication and authorization are dynamic and strictly enforced before access is allowed. Identity verification in zero trust goes beyond traditional username/password by implementing continuous, risk-adaptive authentication using multiple signals including device posture, behavioral biometrics, location, and network context.}

\p{This skill covers implementing phishing-resistant MFA, continuous identity verification, risk-based conditional access, and identity governance aligned with the CISA Zero Trust Maturity Model Identity Pillar.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{When deploying or configuring implementing identity verification for zero trust capabilities in your environment}
\li{When establishing security controls aligned to compliance requirements}
\li{When building or improving security architecture for this domain}
\li{When conducting security assessments that require this implementation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Familiarity with zero trust architecture concepts and tools}
\li{Access to a test or lab environment for safe execution}
\li{Python 3.8+ with required dependencies installed}
\li{Appropriate authorization for any testing activities}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Architecture}
\subtree{
\title{Identity Verification Flow}
\pre{\startverb
User Access Request
    │
    v
┌───────────────────────┐
│ Primary Authentication │
│ - FIDO2/WebAuthn key  │
│ - Certificate-based    │
│ - Passwordless         │
└──────────┬────────────┘
           v
┌───────────────────────┐
│ Contextual Assessment  │
│ - Device posture       │
│ - Network location     │
│ - Geo-velocity check   │
│ - Time of access       │
│ - Behavioral baseline  │
└──────────┬────────────┘
           v
┌───────────────────────┐
│ Risk Scoring Engine    │
│ - Aggregate signals    │
│ - Calculate risk score │
│ - Compare to threshold │
└───┬──────────┬────────┘
    │          │
 Low Risk   High Risk
    │          │
    v          v
┌────────┐  ┌──────────────┐
│ Grant  │  │ Step-up Auth  │
│ Access │  │ - Hardware key│
│        │  │ - Biometric   │
│        │  │ - Manager OK  │
└────────┘  └──────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Identity Provider Architecture}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Primary IdP}: Azure AD / Okta / Ping Identity for centralized identity management}
\li{\strong{FIDO2 Authenticators}: Hardware security keys (YubiKey) or platform authenticators (Windows Hello, Touch ID)}
\li{\strong{Risk Engine}: Adaptive access using identity threat detection (Microsoft Entra ID Protection, Okta ThreatInsight)}
\li{\strong{Identity Governance}: Lifecycle management, access reviews, just-in-time provisioning}
\li{\strong{Privileged Identity}: Separate verification for elevated access (CyberArk, BeyondTrust)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{Phishing-Resistant MFA}
\p{FIDO2/WebAuthn eliminates phishable credentials by binding authentication to the origin domain. Hardware security keys and platform authenticators provide cryptographic proof of identity without transmitting secrets.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Continuous Identity Verification}
\p{Rather than authenticating once at session start, zero trust requires ongoing verification through session token evaluation, behavioral analytics, and periodic re-authentication challenges based on risk signals.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Risk-Based Conditional Access}
\p{Conditional access policies evaluate multiple signals (user risk level, sign-in risk, device compliance, location) to dynamically adjust authentication requirements and access grants.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Identity Threat Detection}
\p{AI-driven analytics detect compromised identities through impossible travel detection, anomalous sign-in patterns, credential stuffing detection, and token replay attacks.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\subtree{
\title{Phase 1: Identity Infrastructure}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Consolidate Identity Providers}}
\li{Audit all identity sources across the organization}
\li{Federate to a single authoritative IdP using SAML 2.0 or OIDC}
\li{Configure SCIM for automated provisioning and deprovisioning}
\li{Eliminate local accounts and shared credentials}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Deploy Phishing-Resistant MFA}}
\li{Enroll all users in FIDO2/WebAuthn with hardware security keys}
\li{Configure platform authenticators (Windows Hello for Business, macOS Touch ID)}
\li{Disable SMS and voice call as MFA methods (phishable)}
\li{Create conditional access policy requiring phishing-resistant methods for all sign-ins}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Configure Conditional Access Policies}}
\li{Require compliant device for access to sensitive applications}
\li{Block legacy authentication protocols (basic auth, IMAP, POP3)}
\li{Require MFA for all users from untrusted locations}
\li{Enforce session time limits with re-authentication}
\li{Block or require additional verification for high-risk sign-ins}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 2: Risk-Based Authentication}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Enable Identity Threat Detection}}
\li{Activate Microsoft Entra ID Protection or Okta ThreatInsight}
\li{Configure risk levels: low (allow), medium (require MFA), high (block and investigate)}
\li{Enable impossible travel detection and anomalous token alerts}
\li{Integrate identity risk signals with SIEM/SOAR}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Implement Step-Up Authentication}}
\li{For sensitive operations (privilege elevation, financial transactions), require additional verification}
\li{Configure step-up policies: re-authenticate with hardware key}
\li{Integrate with PAM for privileged session approval workflows}
\li{Log all step-up events for audit trail}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 3: Continuous Verification}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Deploy Continuous Access Evaluation (CAE)}}
\li{Enable Continuous Access Evaluation Protocol (CAEP) for real-time token revocation}
\li{Configure critical event triggers: user disabled, password changed, location change}
\li{Test that token revocation occurs within minutes (not hours) of security event}
\li{Monitor CAE event logs for operational health}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Implement Session Controls}}
\li{Configure session duration limits based on application sensitivity}
\li{Enable sign-in frequency controls (re-authenticate every N hours)}
\li{Implement persistent browser session controls}
\li{Configure app-enforced restrictions for unmanaged devices}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 4: Identity Governance}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Automate Identity Lifecycle}}
\li{Configure joiner-mover-leaver workflows with HR system integration}
\li{Automate access provisioning based on role and department}
\li{Enable just-in-time access for temporary elevated permissions}
\li{Configure automatic access expiration for contractors and guests}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Implement Access Reviews}}
\li{Schedule quarterly access certification campaigns}
\li{Configure automated reminders and escalation}
\li{Require manager approval for continued access}
\li{Auto-revoke access for unreviewed certifications}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Validation Checklist}
\ul{
\li{[ ] Single authoritative IdP with all applications federated}
\li{[ ] FIDO2/WebAuthn enrolled for all users}
\li{[ ] SMS and voice MFA methods disabled}
\li{[ ] Legacy authentication protocols blocked}
\li{[ ] Conditional access policies enforced for all applications}
\li{[ ] Identity threat detection active with risk-based policies}
\li{[ ] Continuous Access Evaluation enabled and tested}
\li{[ ] Step-up authentication configured for sensitive operations}
\li{[ ] Identity lifecycle automated with HR integration}
\li{[ ] Quarterly access reviews scheduled and operational}
\li{[ ] Identity events streaming to SIEM}
}
}

